divs: sighting detailsthis is sort of a retro-discovery....i was going through some old digital photos and came across one that i took from phoenix skyharbor airport terminal. the photo is from 2005. i remember taking the photo, but i do not remember the phenomena in the sky over the neck and head of camelback mountain. something is either generating light or reflecting the afternoon sun. it is certainly not incoming aircraft as the glidepath for skyharbor is east\west. it could be reflection of light behind me in the terminal, but then i believe i would see other reflections as well across the photo. i do not remember which terminal, but i was flying on northwest. other info photo taken on a sony cybershot dsc-p72 (3.2 mp) flash: not used shutter speed 1\125 date: may 31, 2005 camera time: 6:15 pm (camera was set for eastern daylight time, not phoenix time) so the photo was probably taken at 3:15 pm phoenix time.
